name: Delbáeth

attributes.attribute: believed to be the same as the important goddess of earth, Danu
associated with the mystical hill of Uisneach, where he was said to have built a great Fire from which Five points of light streamed out

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Obscure as she is, Delbáeth is an Irish goddess known as the "fire-shape". Her name is brought up in the Book of Invasions as the mother of Donand, who is believed to be the same as Danu, the significant goddess of earth. Delbáeth's name reappears as a Druid associated with the mystical hill of Uisneach, where he constructed a massive Fire that emitted Five points of light.
